consumer_protection_matrix.exact_code_change:
Replace:
```js
const pq=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('monitor/curmudgeon/priority-queue.json','utf8'));
const recent=pq.history.filter(h=>new Date(h.popped_at)>=cutoff);
```
With:
```js
const readline=require('readline');
const recent=[];
const rl=readline.createInterface({input:fs.createReadStream('monitor/curmudgeon/priority-queue-archive.jsonl')});
await new Promise(res=>{rl.on('line',l=>{const h=JSON.parse(l); if(new Date(h.popped_at)>=cutoff)recent.push(h);});rl.on('close',res);});
```
For synchronous use (no top-level await): `const lines=fs.readFileSync('monitor/curmudgeon/priority-queue-archive.jsonl','utf8').split('\n').filter(Boolean); const recent=lines.map(l=>JSON.parse(l)).filter(h=>new Date(h.popped_at)>=cutoff);`

consumer_protection_matrix.exact_code_change_for_status_update:
Currently in workspace-sync verifier (workspace-sync.md Mech 1):
```js
const c=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('monitor/decisions/closed-issues.json','utf8'));
const issue=c.issues.find(i=>i.id===id); issue.status='fixed';
fs.writeFileSync('monitor/decisions/closed-issues.json',JSON.stringify(c,null,2));
```
New:
```js
fs.appendFileSync('monitor/decisions/closed-issues-archive.jsonl', JSON.stringify({id, status:'fixed', verified_at:new Date().toISOString(), verified_by:'workspace-sync-verifier', supersedes_event:'fixed-pending-verification'})+'\n');
```
Reader (lookup by id) reads `tail -1` of grep matches; the most recent line wins. This matches event-sourcing semantics — old events are immutable, new events represent state transitions.

