Currently in structure-integrity.md collision check:
```js
const t=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('monitor/analyst/expansion-tracker.json','utf8'));
const dup=t.items.filter(i=>i.id===id);
```
New:
```js
const t=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('monitor/analyst/expansion-tracker.json','utf8'));
const liveDup=t.items.filter(i=>i.id===id);
const archDup=execSync(\`grep '"id":"${id}"' monitor/analyst/expansion-tracker-archive.jsonl 2>/dev/null || true\`,{encoding:'utf8'}).split('\n').filter(Boolean).map(l=>JSON.parse(l));
const dup=[...liveDup, ...archDup];
```
Note: collision detection is daily, not per-run; wall-clock cost is tolerable.
